message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Maldives, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you enjoy walking, you can simply walk to the grocery store. It will take approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling can be a convenient and quick way to reach the grocery store. It will take around 5-10 minutes to cover the distance.

3. Public Transportation: Check if there are any local buses or public transportation options available in your area. They might have routes passing by or near the grocery store. You can inquire about the nearest bus stop and take a bus to reach your destination.

4. Taxi: Taxis are readily available in Maldives, and you can easily find one to take you to the grocery store. It will be a quick and convenient option, but keep in mind that it might be slightly more expensive than other modes of transportation.

Consider the weather, your preferences, and the availability of transportation options to choose the most suitable method for your journey to the grocery store.
